Package: bikeCadHr
Type: Package
Title: Analyze Cycling Cadence Data From GPS .fit and .gpx Files
Version: 0.9.0
Date: 2017-12-07
Author: Craig Mohn
Maintainer: Craig Mohn <craig.mohn.projects@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 2.15.0)
Imports: magrittr, dplyr, tibble, lubridate, stringr,
    XML, fitdc, raster, OpenStreetMap, mapproj, ggplot2, viridis, scales, 
    doParallel, foreach, parallel, plotly, htmlwidgets, rgl
Description: Functions to process and clean up .fit and .gpx files containing
    cadence and heart rate data.  Store the data in pairs of tibbles, one 
    containing summary data about the ride, the other containing the track
    points.  Plot an information-dense graphic allowing quick visual appraisal
    of the relationships between cadence, heartrate, speed and terrain.  
    Generate maps of a ride or set of rides, using user-defined map bounds
    if desired.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
